lead_paragraph: CBS garnered the highest ratings on Thursday as “Survivor” and “CSI” topped Fox’s coverage of the World Series. According to Nielsen’s estimates, “CSI” earned the night’s largest audience as 19.2 million viewers tuned in to the crime drama at 9 p.m. It followed a strong showing during the 8 p.m. hour for CBS’s “Survivor: Gabon” (13.4 million). At 10 p.m., CBS’s new show “Eleventh Hour” drew a solid 12.2 million viewers.

headline.main: Ratings: ‘Kath & Kim,’ ‘The Office,’ ‘SNL’ in Fourth Place on Thursday
